### Web Fonts

**Web fonts** let you use custom fonts not installed on the user's computer.

---

### Google Fonts

The easiest way to add custom fonts:

```html
<!-- Add in <head> -->
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

```css
body {
  font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
}
```

---

### @font-face

Host your own font files:

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'MyFont';
  src: url('myfont.woff2') format('woff2'),
       url('myfont.woff') format('woff');
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

body {
  font-family: 'MyFont', sans-serif;
}
```

---

### Font Formats

| Format | Extension | Browser Support |
|--------|-----------|----------------|
| **WOFF2** | `.woff2` | Best modern format |
| **WOFF** | `.woff` | Wide support |
| TTF/OTF | `.ttf` / `.otf` | Legacy |
| EOT | `.eot` | Old IE only |
| SVG | `.svg` | Old Safari |

**Best Practice:** Use WOFF2 with WOFF fallback.

---

### Font Display

Controls how font loads:

```css
@font-face {
  font-display: swap;     /* Show fallback, swap when loaded */
  font-display: block;    /* Invisible until loaded */
  font-display: fallback; /* Short swap period */
  font-display: optional; /* Only use if already loaded */
}
```

`font-display: swap` is recommended for most sites.

---

### Variable Fonts

One file contains multiple weights/styles:

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('Inter-Variable.woff2') format('woff2-variations');
  font-weight: 100 900;
}

h1 {
  font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  font-weight: 700; /* Any weight 100-900 */
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Use Google Fonts for simplicity. Use `@font-face` + WOFF2 for custom fonts. Always include a fallback generic family.
